\par Polaris considers email as an important means of communication and recognises the importance of proper email content and speedy replies in conveying a professional image and delivering good customer service. Therefore, the Organisation wishes users to adh
ere to the following guidelines:
\par 
\par {\listtext\pard\plain\ltrpar \s42 \rtlch\fcs1 \af42\afs20\alang1037 \ltrch\fcs0 \f3\fs16\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8860867\charrsid2578727 \loch\af3\dbch\af0\hich\f3 \'b7\tab}}\pard\plain \ltrpar\s42\ql \fi-284\li284\ri86\sb67\widctlpar
\tx-450\tx-180\jclisttab\tx284\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\ls49\nosnaplinegrid\adjustright\rin86\lin284\itap0\pararsid8860867 \rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs20\alang1037 \ltrch\fcs0 \f45\fs16\lang2057\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp2057\langfenp1033 {\rtlch\fcs1 
\af42 \ltrch\fcs0 \f31506\insrsid8860867\charrsid2578727 Write well-structured emails and use short, descriptive subjects.
\par {\listtext\pard\plain\ltrpar \s42 \rtlch\fcs1 \af42\afs20\alang1037 \ltrch\fcs0 \f3\fs16\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8860867\charrsid2578727 \loch\af3\dbch\af0\hich\f3 \'b7\tab}The Organisation\rquote 
s email style is informal. This means that sentences can be short and to the point. You can start your email with \lquote Hi\rquote , or \lquote Dear\rquote , and the name of the person. Messages can be ended with \lquote Best Regards\rquote 
. The use of abbreviations and characters such as smileys, however, is not encouraged.
\par {\listtext\pard\plain\ltrpar \s42 \rtlch\fcs1 \af42\afs20\alang1037 \ltrch\fcs0 \f3\fs16\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8860867\charrsid2578727 \loch\af3\dbch\af0\hich\f3 \'b7\tab}Signatures must include your name, job title and Organisation name. 

\par {\listtext\pard\plain\ltrpar \s42 \rtlch\fcs1 \af42\afs20\alang1037 \ltrch\fcs0 \f3\fs16\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8860867\charrsid2578727 \loch\af3\dbch\af0\hich\f3 \'b7\tab}Use the spell checker before you send out an email.
\par {\listtext\pard\plain\ltrpar \s42 \rtlch\fcs1 \af42\afs20\alang1037 \ltrch\fcs0 \f3\fs16\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8860867\charrsid2578727 \loch\af3\dbch\af0\hich\f3 \'b7\tab}Do not send unnecessary attachments.
\par {\listtext\pard\plain\ltrpar \s42 \rtlch\fcs1 \af42\afs20\alang1037 \ltrch\fcs0 \f3\fs16\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8860867\charrsid2578727 \loch\af3\dbch\af0\hich\f3 \'b7\tab}
Do not write emails in capitals.  This appears as if you are shouting and is considered rude.
\par {\listtext\pard\plain\ltrpar \s42 \rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af42\afs20\alang1037 \ltrch\fcs0 \f3\fs16\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8860867\charrsid2578727 \loch\af3\dbch\af0\hich\f3 \'b7\tab}}{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af42 \ltrch\fcs0 
\b\f31506\insrsid8860867\charrsid2578727 Do not print emails unless you really need to for work purposes}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af42 \ltrch\fcs0 \f31506\insrsid8860867\charrsid2578727 .  Emails can be saved, if you need them.
\par {\listtext\pard\plain\ltrpar \s42 \rtlch\fcs1 \af42\afs20\alang1037 \ltrch\fcs0 \f3\fs16\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8860867\charrsid2578727 \loch\af3\dbch\af0\hich\f3 \'b7\tab}
If you need a reply to your email by a particular date let the recipient know this.
\par {\listtext\pard\plain\ltrpar \s42 \rtlch\fcs1 \af42\afs20\alang1037 \ltrch\fcs0 \f3\fs16\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8860867\charrsid2578727 \loch\af3\dbch\af0\hich\f3 \'b7\tab}
If you forward mails, state clearly what action you expect the recipient to take.
\par {\listtext\pard\plain\ltrpar \s42 \rtlch\fcs1 \af42\afs20\alang1037 \ltrch\fcs0 \f3\fs16\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8860867\charrsid2578727 \loch\af3\dbch\af0\hich\f3 \'b7\tab}
