\b\i\f1\fs28\lang2057\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp2057\langfenp1033 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af42\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \i0\f31506\fs24\insrsid11800560\charrsid2578727 5. Use Proper Salutations
\par }\pard\plain \ltrpar\ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid3687428 \rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs20\alang1025 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\fs20\lang2057\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp2057\langfenp1033 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af42 \ltrch\fcs0 
\f31506\insrsid11800560\charrsid2578727 It\rquote s important to understand how to introduce yourself in an email and how to start a professional email with the right salutation, especially when you\rquote 
re emailing someone for the first time or for professional reasons. We recommend sticking to the \'93Hello ,\'94 or \'93Hi ,\'94 professional email greetings for most emails, unless you know the recipient well enough to go with \'93Hey\'94 or \'93Yo\'94.

\par In most cases, if you\rquote re emailing back and forth with the same recipient, you can even drop the \lquote Hi\rquote s and \lquote Hello\rquote s after a few replies.
\par Similarly, it is just as important to understand how to end a
n email professionally. When writing in a professional email format, you need to be careful about your professional email sign off, as making a mistake there will not just lead to your email getting ignored, but also might result in the recipient getting 
disinterested in emails from you.
\par }\pard\plain \ltrpar\s2\ql \li0\ri0\sl500\slmult0\keepn\widctlpar\wrapdefault\faauto\outlinelevel1\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid11800560 \rtlch\fcs1 \ab\ai\af1\afs28\alang1025 \ltrch\fcs0 
\b\i\f1\fs28\lang2057\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp2057\langfenp1033 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af42\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \i0\f31506\fs24\insrsid11800560\charrsid2578727 6. Use the Reply-All Option Carefully
\par }\pard\plain \ltrpar\ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid3687428 \rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs20\alang1025 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\fs20\lang2057\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp2057\langfenp1033 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af42 \ltrch\fcs0 
\f31506\insrsid11800560\charrsid2578727 Email overload is already a major issue for most users these days and no one wants to read or process email that isn\rquote 
t intended for them. Our smartphones, tablets, and computers can go crazy with notifications about the same email, and it\rquote s critical that 
we get some email sanity. As a result, you should always be careful when you use the Reply All option. If you have just received an email that has multiple people in the CC field, take a moment and consider whether your reply will be relevant to them. 

\par In most cases, your email response is only intended for a single person, like a question about something mentioned in the previous email. In such cases, just use the \lquote Reply\rquote  button instead of \lquote Reply All\rquote .
\par }\pard\plain \ltrpar\s2\ql \li0\ri0\sl500\slmult0\keepn\widctlpar\wrapdefault\faauto\outlinelevel1\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid11800560 \rtlch\fcs1 \ab\ai\af1\afs28\alang1025 \ltrch\fcs0 
