\par }\pard\plain \ltrpar\ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid3687428 \rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs20\alang1025 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\fs20\lang2057\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp2057\langfenp1033 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af42 \ltrch\fcs0 
\f31506\insrsid11800560\charrsid2578727 Many times, often in a work environment, you\rquote ll need to forward an email to someone who wasn\rquote 
t part of the original email chain. They may need to copy some information from the email, or view something for reference. In such cases, it is a good practice to clean up your email before forwarding it to someone.
\par Pay special attention to any sensitive information mentioned in the email history that you don\rquote t want others to see and manually delete it. Remove any \'93Fwd: Fwd: Fwd:\'94
 characters from the subject line, and redact any private information such as client addresses, phone numbers or email addresses.
\par }\pard\plain \ltrpar\s2\ql \li0\ri0\sl500\slmult0\keepn\widctlpar\wrapdefault\faauto\outlinelevel1\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid11800560 \rtlch\fcs1 \ab\ai\af1\afs28\alang1025 \ltrch\fcs0 
