Think of your email inbox as your desk at work. Your emails are like the physical paper files that you work with. The files that you are currently working on stay on your desk, so they are easily accessible when you need to refer something or file somethi
ng new in them. The files for projects that you are done working on are moved to the storage cabinet, right?
\par We recommend looking at your emails in the same way. The emails that you are done reading and responding to, or don\rquote t need to bother with again (such as email newsletters or purchase confirmations) can be \'93Archived\'94
, i.e. moved away to a different section and making space for new ones. This way, your email inbox stays clutter-free and you can focus on the emails that are pending.
\par Along the same lines, Spark offers additional functionality such as the ability to }{\field\fldedit{\*\fldinst {\rtlch\fcs1 \af42 \ltrch\fcs0 \f31506\insrsid11800560\charrsid2578727  HYPERLINK "https://sparkmailapp.com/features/snooze" }{\rtlch\fcs1 
