\par }\pard\plain \ltrpar\ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid3687428 \rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs20\alang1025 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\fs20\lang2057\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp2057\langfenp1033 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af42 \ltrch\fcs0 
\f31506\insrsid11800560\charrsid2578727 We\rquote ve kept the most important point for the end, and that\rquote s to double-check the recipient. With auto-complete features and an ever-extending address book, it\rquote 
s easy to mix-up recipients and to end up sending the wrong email to someone. To avoid this, we recommend filling out the To: field after you\rquote re done composing and formatting your email. This way, you also don\rquote 
t mistakenly hit the Send button or shortcut and send an email away with less than half the text that you actually wanted to send.
\par Remember, email is still a core tool of communication across the internet, so it\rquote s important to take it seriously. We hope these 12 tips are helpful to you when you start composing your next email. Did we miss anything?
